'''Brook Glacier''' ({{Coord|78|42|S|85|09|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] that flows westward between [[Mount Strybing]], [[Mount Allen (Antarctica)|Mount Allen]] and [[Krusha Peak]] on the west side of [[Owen Ridge]] in southern [[Sentinel Range]], [[Ellsworth Mountains]] in [[Antarctica]], and joins [[Bender Glacier]] east of [[Chaplin Peak]]. It was named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] (2006) after [[Edward J. Brook]], Professor of Geosciences, [[Oregon State University]]; [[United States Antarctic Program|U.S. Antarctic Project]] investigator of Antarctic paleoclimate in numerous field seasons from 1988; Chair, U.S. National Ice Core Working Group for use of Antarctic ice cores for research purposes, 2004–05.
